719572f-a.title: Manhattan: East River Drive - Gracie Square
719572f-a.text:
East River Drive, at Gracie Square
(East 84th Street) showing constructional
details depicted by a series of oils by Mrs.
Tohn Markell. These were on display at the
Municipal Reference Library from April 15th
to the 30th of 1940. Titles of same are:
From Beekman Place, Smoke, and Sunrise.
The arched span in the background is the
Hellgate Bridge. Preceeding same is the
horizontal Triboro Bridge. To the right is
Astoria in the Borough of Cueens.
1939

showing constructional details depicted by a series of oils

719576f-b.title: Manhattan: East River Drive - Gracie Square
719576f-b.text:
Fast River Drive, at Gracie Souare (Eaat 84th
Street) showing constructional details depicted
by a series of oils by Mrs. John Markell. These
were on display at the Municipal Heference Library
from April 15th to the 30th of 1940. Titles of
same are: Drivers, Hoisting cement blocks, The
little green tug and "Buggies." This formed the
first stage, the seawall. Constructed by the
Federal Government, it enclosed a fill upon
which was erected the double decker roadway
skirting Carl Schurs Park. In the hackground is
Welfare Island and the Sueensboro Pridge.
1939
